<br>
I have a Wurmy, a JBoM and a Centi LS. Have been running with Wurmy in pri and Centi in sec and like the Wurmy's big hits. However, my understanding is that the speed of the pri weapon will gate the DW hits and DA hits for sec weapon. Is this accurate? If so, I am considering replacing (slow) Wurmy with JBoM (thus, JBoM pri and Centi sec) so that the much faster JBoM will result in more DW hits from offhander, even if pri hits are for lower damage, resulting in better overall DPS.<br>
<br>
Comments on this? Also suggestions as to how this might change as I move through levels - at 45? at 50? <br>
<br>
Also, any suggestions on how differing melee scenarios I run into over the next 10 levels or so might require differing strategies (hot swapping of weapons)?<br>
<br>
Also, what 1HS weapon upgrades should I be looking at for near future (bearing in mind that I have no cash machine toon and need to upgrade via loot sales and current weapon sales)? That is, I won't be buying a SBoZ anytime soon! Seems to me that 1HS wpns are either &lt;2kpp or &gt;8kpp for the most part. :-(<br>
<br>
Finally, whats a good parser that will give me DPS and other useful info and where can I find it?<br>
<br>
TIA for your attention and insights.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=takeshimonogatari>Takeshi Monogatari</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mminternet.com/~johnlongmore/note.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/02 12:55:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4418.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mminternet.com/~johnlongmore/notes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Low 40s warrior - which wpn in which slot?</span><hr size=1> Dual Wield doesn't work like that.  Your offhand checks your DW skill every time the delay on the weapon cycles, and if you pass the skill check your weapon swings.  It is completely independent of your primary weapon.<br>
<br>
Fast weapons are preferred in primary hand due to the way damage bonuses work.  Each hit has the bonus added for your main hand weapon.  More primary hand hits -&gt; more times that the damage bonus is applied.  Once the damage bonus starts getting big it can cause low delay weapons with a worse ratio to outdamage a slower, better ratio weapon. <p>Takeshi Monogatari<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Non-Druid<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Druzzil Ro<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.mminternet.com/~johnlongmore/nondruid.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dagnarok>dagnarok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/02 10:23:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4418.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Low 40s warrior - which wpn in which slot?</span><hr size=1> OK, in that case, since both the Wurmy and the JBoM have a damage bonus of 5, then it would seem that using the faster weapon - JBoM - would result in more hits and therefore damage bonus will be applied more often adding up to more overall damage. Or is the damage bonus you are talking about different than the weapon damage bonus?<br>
<br>
However, since ratio of Wurmy - 1.6 - is significantly better that JBoM- 1.923 - the Wurmy would normally outdamage the JBoM without considering the damage bonus so that would have to be considered, too, right?<br>
<br>
Thus the advantage here is difficult to determine since I don't know which is better: higher dmg of wurmy due to ratio or higher damage of JBoM due to more bonus damage being achieved. I would *guess* that the Wurmy wins this one.<br>
<br>
Also, I would look at other relevant weapon stats:<br>
<br>
Wurmy: AC 5 STR+5<br>
JBoM: AC 3 DEX+10<br>
<br>
On this basis alone, looks like Wurmy wins out since it raises my max dmg cap via the STR boost as well as adding +2 net AC, and the JBoM's dex does not come into play since neither weapon has a proc. (A lot of crusty = dex of 62 on my warrior btw)<br>
<br>
Is that right? <br>
<br>
Thanks very much for taking the time to explain things to a somewhat bewildered warrior! ;-)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=visiyavelverothe>Visiya VelveRothe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/02 12:10:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4418.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: low 40s warrior</span><hr size=1> Well, frankly, looking for the big, pretty hits isn't going to get you very far.  Can you hold aggro with the weapons you have?  If you can, no one can really say anything.  That said, I'd be surprised if you could with a wurmslayer in your primary slot.<br>
<br>
They're both pretty slow, but I'd say that you're reaching the threshold of where the Wurmslayer is still a productive weapon for you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cslochraven>CSLochraven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 265<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/02 12:34:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4418.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gs.cdnow.com/graphics/COVERART/local/L/80/01/00138001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: low 40s warrior</span><hr size=1> You are correct with your thought of JBoM primary and Centi LS secondary.  <br>
<br>
Wurmslayers should be removed from the game.  They suck. <p>&lt;b&gt;Lochraven&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;<br>
Warlord&lt;br&gt;<br>
The Nameless<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=takeshimonogatari>Takeshi Monogatari</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mminternet.com/~johnlongmore/note.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/17/02 12:42:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4418.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mminternet.com/~johnlongmore/notes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: low 40s warrior</span><hr size=1> Aye, I was referring to the &quot;damage bonus&quot; value listed on your weapons.  This is level dependent for 1h weapons, and both level and delay dependent for 2h weapons.<br>
<br>
For a good example of when speed is important in weapon selection you can look at some of the Luclin bosses (not that I've ever fought one, but I've read enough about it) which have very high AC values.  A high percentage of meele hits against that type of mob land for the minimum value, usually (1 + bonus).  So a level 60 character will hit for 12 damage.  In this case the majority of the damage comes from the bonus, which is independent of the damage and delay values on the weapon (for 1h weapons), so the faster you hit the more damage you do.<br>
<br>
Faster hits are also generally thought to generate more hate with a mob than slower, higher damage hits.<br>
<br>
The extra stat bonuses on your weapons of choice are of secondary concern, imo.  A few ac or str or dex aren't going to affect your performance as much as the interplay of dam, delay, and bonus (the extra +5 MR on the JBoM is big, though).  You aren't going to find alot of WS fans around here I think, but at early levels it is a good weapon.  I think you are right around the level where speed really becomes a factor, though. <p>Takeshi Monogatari<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Non-Druid<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Druzzil Ro<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.mminternet.com/~johnlongmore/nondruid.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
